28/10/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- New federal Defence Minister Zoran Stankovic said in a TV interview on Thursday (27 October) that he will seek written reports from all relevant institutions searching for Ratko Mladic, to confirm that they have no information about his whereabouts. Stankovic again said he has no personal knowledge of the fugitive war crimes indictee's location, insisting the last time he saw Mladic was in 1999. 
In other news, the Serbia-Montenegro Parliament votes on Friday on an agreement that would allow NATO troops to use Serbia as a transit country for its operations. Based on the statements of various party officials, approval is expected. Supporters view it as a step towards eventual membership in NATO's Partnership for Peace programme. (Vecernje Novosti, Glas Javnosti - 28/10/05; B92, RTS, Tanjug, Beta - 27/10/05; BK TV - 26/10/05)
